“ Oh, I hope you’ll die in a garretl starved
to death,” said the boy, mistaking our approach
for that of his negligent attendant.

He stopped, on observing his error; his cou-
sin ﬂew to him.

“ Is that you, Miss Linton?” he said, rais-
ing his head from the arm of the great chair,
in which he reclined. “ No—don’t kiss me.
It takes my breath—dear me ! Papa said you
